ET, April 13 —Bernie Sanders has finally offered his full-throated endorsement of Joe Biden‘s campaign for president.
“We need you in the White House,” Sanders told Biden on the live stream.
https://t.co/MYc7kt2b16 — Bernie Sanders (@BernieSanders) April 8, 2020The move cleared the way for former Biden to become the Democratic nominee.
A poll in January showed that more than half of Sanders’ supporters said they would definitely support the Democratic nominee if it’s not Bernie, Newsweek reported.
The share of Black voters fell decidedly in 2016 compared to 2012, according to statistics compiled by the Center for American Progress, an independent nonpartisan nonprofit organization.